A Zonal Coordinator of the APC in Sokoto East, Alhaji Shaaya Musa Gwadabawa, yesterday, called on the Senator representing Sokoto East, Dr. Ibrahim Abdullahi Gobir, to declare for the deputy senate presidency. Alhaji Gwadabawa said considering his contributions to national issues and other vital discussions in the red chamber, Sen. Gobir possessed all the qualities and qualifications to be the deputy senate president. Gwadabawa added that the call was premised on the senator’s track record of good representation. Commenting on the call, Sen. Gobir noted that leaders were chosen by God, adding that he would wait for Allah’s decision on that. Muhammadu Zayyana, father of Sokoto Speaker, dies 2015 politics: apc bigwigs storm sokoto for tambuwal APC's Senator Gobir retains seat, defeats Sokoto Assembly Speaker Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin